com.foursquare.geo.shapes

Class LabeledGridSimplifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foursquare.geo.shapes.LabeledGridSimplifier

  • public class LabeledGridSimplifier
extends java.lang.Object
    Simplifies a Shapefile by perfoming two actions: 1. splits the features of the Shapefile into a grid according to the reference levelSizes. 2. if all features within a cell of the grid have the same label (value of keyName attribute), all features of that cell are replaced by a simple rectangle of the cell's bounds.

      • simplify

        public static java.lang.Iterable<FeatureEntry> simplify(CellLocationReference reference,
                                                        java.util.List<FeatureEntry> features,
                                                        boolean simplifySingleLabelCells)
        Simplify the set of features.
        Parameters:
        reference - the location reference (bounding box, etc)
        features - the input set of features
        simplifySingleLabelCells - when false, no simplification is performed, location index attributes are generated (for fast lookup when loaded), and shapes are split by the requested levelSizes, but when shapes within a cell all share the same label, the cell will not be replaced with a simple rectangle see SimplifiedShapefileGeo.load(java.net.URL, java.lang.String, boolean) keepGeometry.
        Returns:
        a set of simplified features
